    <note type="dates"><date>1818–71</date></note>
    <sex value="M"/>
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Journalist and beekeeper. From 1850 devoted himself exclusively to beekeeping. Introduced Ligurian bees to Britain in 1859 and developed the "Woodbury hive", marketed by the London apiarian specialists George Neighbour &amp; Sons. As "A Devonshire Beekeeper", a regular contributor to the <hi rend="italic">Cottage Gardener</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">Journal of Horticulture</hi>, the <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi>, and <hi rend="italic">The Times.</hi></p></note>
    <note type="sources">
        <p>R. H. Brown 1975, Ron Brown 1994, Dodd 1983, H. M. Fraser 1958, Neighbour 1865.</p>
    </note>
